history.content: If there is still space at that time (both in the lecture and in the assigned discussion section), this could work.

I want to be a part of a team with my friends taking CS169 in Fall '16. They have 5 members right now and all of them have wait-listed for the class Phase 1. I cannot phase 1 this class but if I am able to get in phase 2, I want to join that team.

Is it possible to join a specific team in phase 2? Should I fill out the google form with them right now? Or should I approach this later?

I understand that I run the risk of not getting into the class. However, if I am able to enroll into the class, would I be able to join that team because they would still have one spot left. The course website only discussed cases of students dropping the class so I want to confirm this here.

Thanks!
